23:29.930 --> 23:32.190
Your breakfast,
Mrs. Waterford.

23:32.190 --> 23:35.030
I'm still full from dinner.

23:35.030 --> 23:37.870
Well, for the flight then.

23:37.870 --> 23:39.890
Do you think
that she'll like it?

23:53.440 --> 23:55.870
"For this child
I prayed."

23:59.920 --> 24:01.720
Oh, it's beautiful.

24:05.250 --> 24:07.700
Would you give her a kiss
from me, please?

24:10.330 --> 24:12.730
Of course.

24:22.470 --> 24:24.640
Ma'am, there's something else.

24:24.640 --> 24:26.680
It arrived last night.

24:29.680 --> 24:31.550
What is it?

24:31.550 --> 24:33.580
It didn't have
my name on it, ma'am.

24:39.020 --> 24:40.030
The car is here.

24:41.680 --> 24:43.130
I'll wrap this up
for the flight.

24:43.130 --> 24:44.550
Thank you, Rita.

25:17.840 --> 25:18.880
Let's go.

25:54.460 --> 25:55.590
Blessed day,
Mrs. Waterford.

25:56.660 --> 25:57.880
Under His eye.

26:21.040 --> 26:23.210
Mrs. Waterford.

26:23.210 --> 26:25.220
Welcome.

26:28.440 --> 26:30.570
Mr. Tuello.

26:30.570 --> 26:32.870
You remember me.
I'm flattered.

26:32.870 --> 26:35.880
I'm just here to make sure
this goes smoothly.

26:37.250 --> 26:39.180
I know how to conduct myself.

26:40.030 --> 26:42.080
Mr. Tuello will take it
from here.

26:42.080 --> 26:44.220
The Commander
gave me strict orders.

26:44.220 --> 26:45.440
I speak for the Commander

26:45.440 --> 26:46.750
in his absence.

26:46.750 --> 26:49.460
Yes, Mrs. Waterford.

26:49.460 --> 26:51.260
It's a short drive
to the terminal.

26:51.260 --> 26:52.880
You'll change there.

26:52.880 --> 26:54.030
I'm sorry?

26:54.030 --> 26:55.050
Mr. Bankole
requested

26:55.050 --> 26:57.010
a more public meeting place.

26:57.900 --> 27:00.870
We brought you
a change of clothes.

